"content": "<h2>The ancestors of Israel</h2>\n<h3>Abraham, Isaac and Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:45\">LEV 26:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:21\">JAS 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>More immediate forebears</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:4\">AMO 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:3-1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:3–19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:17\">ACT 28:17</a></p>\n<h2>Ancestors of specific groups of people</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:1\">JOS 17:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen10:21\">GEN 10:21</a></p>\n<h2>Ancestors of individuals</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:5\">ROM 9:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:10\">HEB 7:10</a></p>\n<h2>The figurative use of ancestors</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:3\">EZK 16:3</a></strong></p>",
